eeds domestic matters straying across scales to justify public expenditure cuts. Through a wide range of ethnographic contexts this book explores how practices and moralities of thrift are intertwined with austerity, debt, welfare, and patronage across various social and temporal scales and are constantly re-negotiated at the nexus of socio-economic, religious, and kinship ideals and praxis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aConsumption (Economics)xSocial aspects. 0aSaving and investment. 0aThriftiness. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aPolitical and Economic Anthropology, Sociology.1 aAlexander, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlexander, Catherine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDiz, Agustin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGudeman, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHann, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJames, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeves, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRakowski, Tomasz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRudnyckyj, Daromir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSosna, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSosna, Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSpalová, Barbora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTorkelson, Erin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilk, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyte